# NorDug Presentation - HTML Structure

## Primary Delivery

The main presentation is **Presentation-HTML/index.html** – a Reveal.js 4.3.1 slideshow. Open it in a browser for presentation mode.

## Slide Structure

Each slide is a `<section>` inside `<div class="slides">`:

```html
<!-- SLIDE N: Title -->
<section>
    <img src="images/dEdge.png" class="logo">
    <h2>Slide Title</h2>
    <!-- content -->
</section>
```

## Layout Classes

| Class | Use |
|-------|-----|
| `title-slide` | Centered title slide (slide 1, 25) |
| `section-slide` | Section divider (centered heading) |
| `grid-2`, `grid-3`, `grid-4` | Multi-column layouts |
| `card` | Content block; add `.orange`, `.red`, `.green` for emphasis |
| `stat` | Metric box (number + label) |
| `timeline` / `timeline-item` | Sequential items |
| `diagram` | Wraps diagram images |
| `center` | Center text |
| `small` | Smaller font |

## Diagram Slides

Diagrams live in `Presentation-HTML/diagrams/` as `.mmd` (Mermaid) → `.svg`. Reference in HTML:

```html
<div class="diagram">
    <img src="diagrams/name.svg" alt="Description">
</div>
```

## Slide Numbering

Slides are numbered 1–25. Comments like `<!-- SLIDE N: Title -->` must match the logical order.
